    old "Your arrival, and especially the dragon bone you pull out, are cheerfully welcomed. The guards prepare a couple of wooden planks, which are leaned against the wall. There are also spectators, and you’re told that the other hunters are either sleeping, or have duty on the tower. “Remember, no magic,” says one of the players. His face is deadly serious. \n\nThere’s going to be four participants and eight rounds. You aim at the target drawn with charcoal. The person whose axe lands the closest to the center of the circle gets a point. Axes that fail to stay in the plank don’t count. The person who has the most points at the end of the last turn becomes the winner. "
