    # game/areas/peltnorth2guards.rpy:869
    old "“Their good side, you say... Well, they’re protectors of humans, you know? You shall honor their work en sacrifice. Be honest, but look at the ground en don’t waste their time. Act as if there’s a burden on you en you {i}need them{/i} to help you. En remember to call them {i}forest speakers{/i}! ‘Tis a sign of respect. A simple {i}greetings, forest speaker{/i} will be enough.” \n\nHe points west. “To find them, just stay on the road. You’ll get to a large tree. From there, the road goes north, but there’s a small path south, to a cave. This is where you can find the elder druids, there’s two of them. The others are in {color=#f6d6bd}Howler’s{/color}.” "
